    "narrative": "The offensive core for Ghost Ride the WHIP centers on the high-upside matchup for **Corbin Carroll** (87.14), who remains our premier asset today against Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1rquez. The combination of an elite matchup against a 5.26 xERA starter and the presence of a \"slow\" pitcher who struggles to hold runners makes **Corbin Carroll** the runaway play, as we look to exploit the league\u2019s scarcest category: stolen bases. Following him, **Seiya Suzuki** (68.49) provides a significant surge in our projections; he benefits from a massive 19% SP skill adjustment against Roki Sasaki and favorable wind conditions that favor his profile today. **Brice Turang** (65.25) is also a cornerstone start, anchoring the leadoff spot with a +10% order adjustment that maximizes his potential for runs and stolen base opportunities against Mitch Keller.\n\nWhile our primary lineup is locked in, the bench decision regarding **Max Muncy** (49.36) was the most difficult. **Max Muncy** narrowly missed the final utility slot, losing out to the overall efficiency scores of **Josh Naylor** (60.52) and **Trevor Story** (62.07). The optimizer favored the latter due to **Trevor Story**\u2019s significant park-factor boost (+16%), which outweighed **Max Muncy**\u2019s situational platoon advantages. Furthermore, we continue to monitor the risk inherent in today\u2019s slate as most of the lineup remains \"Pending.\" Any official word that pushes **Luis Campusano** or **Alex Freeland** down the order could trigger a pivot, as their current efficiency scores are already hovering near the bottom of our playable threshold. \n\nWe are also exercising extreme caution with our reserve depth. The rainout of **Mickey Moniak** serves as a stark reminder of the volatility in today\u2019s schedule. While we considered **Austin Riley** as an alternative to mitigate risk against high-end arms, his matchup against a sub-3.00 xERA ace like Zack Wheeler suppressed his score to 45.07, keeping him firmly on the bench alongside **Jose Caballero**. We will continue to track the status of **Gabriel Moreno**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Kyle Karros**, **Carson Williams**, and **Travis Bazzana** to ensure our roster depth remains optimized for the duration of this series.",
